-- U.S. Charges 107 in $452 Million Health-Care Fraud Crackdown
-- B y   S e t h   S t e r n
-- 2012-05-02T18:01:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/u-s-charges-107-in-452-million-health-care-fraud-crackdown.html
The U.S. charged 107 doctors, nurses
and others for allegedly playing a role in Medicare fraud
involving $452 million in bogus bills to the government.  The charges, in unrelated cases across the country, were
part of a crackdown, the  Justice Department  said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Seth Stern in Washington at 
